Shocking revelations by a foreign firm on how it secured sh.180million Kenya Medical Supplies tender stunned members of The National Assembly Public Investment Committee (PIC). Gideon Simiyu, the sole agent of Deekay relief limited narrated how he walked into the agency offices and won the tender amounting to a whooping sh180million, surprisingly, he cannot remember the person that engaged him and took his samples. Simiyu who is an agent of the company&rsquo;s Director Manpreet Signh Kohli said that he walked into KEMSA and talked to &ldquo;a lady&rdquo; that he could not recall and informed her of the items he had.
